headline.main: STALIN RECEIVES U.S. BRITISH AIDES; Harriman and Beaverbrook Visit the Kremlin -- London's Tank Output Up 20% STALIN RECEIVES U.S., BRITISH AIDES

lead_paragraph: MOSCOW, Sept. 28 -- W. Averell Harriman and Lord Beaverbrook and their staffs and the Anglo-American delegations to the Tri-Power Economic Conference in Moscow arrived today on the eve of the opening sessions of talks designed to facilitate supplies for the Soviet fighting forces in the war against Reichsfuehrer Hitler's Germany and to add to the vast resources at the disposal of this country the reserves and manufacturing output of the English-speaking world.
